5] STRING Data types
 1)Anything we write inside '' or "" is nothing but string data in python

Note:
    1)There is no char data type in python.
    2)if specify anything in '' or"" is sting.

Syntax:
  var_name = "value"

e.g.
  c = '10'
  type(c) # <class 'str'>

  s = "python"
  type(s) # <class 'str'>


** Memory Representation :
by using array , 0 to n

 I N S T A G R A M
 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8
 ---------------->
 left to right

 1> Python supports 0 base indexing
 2> There are two types of indexing
        i) forword/ +ve
        ii) Reverse/ -ve
        iii) -ve /Reverse indexing start with -1, Right ot left

 I   N   S   T   A   G   R   A   M
 -9 -8  -7  -6  -5  -4  -3  -2  -1
   <-----------------------
   right to left

# WAP to print element from given string from its index value.Ask user to enter index value

a = "Instagram"
b = int(input("index"))
print(a[b])

** accessing value using index
   - To fetch single element from string we can use indexing

   Syntax:
    var_name = "value"
    var_name[index_value]

** slice on string
-To fetch multiple elements from string we can use slice
Syntax:
  var_name = "value"
  var_name = [start_index:end_index]

e.g.
s = "Instagram"
print(s[1 : 6])
print(s[-1 : -5])
print(s[1 : 6])
print(s[6 : -7])

