** PM on syntax:
    stn :
       var_name[start:end]

i) start value is optional and default start index is 0
 sty :
   varname[ :stop] # This slice return 0 to stop_index -1 elements
  e.g.
  s = "INSTAGRAM"
  print(s[:7])

ii) End index is optional and default and index is -1 or len(s)-1
 sty :
 varname[start_index:] # This slice will return start_index to len(str)-1 element

 iii) Start index and stop index are both optional

 sty :
    varname[:] #this will return complete str



  iv) step size in slice:
  step size is also optional and default value of step size is +1
***imp***
step size in slice:
    syntax:
        varname = [start_index : stop_index : step_size]

